Subject:    bombarded by wildcards!
From:       <a href="?a=95837785800011&r=1&w=2">mailrus!ulowell!page () ames ! arc ! nasa ! gov  (Bob Page)</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198810">1988-10-31 18:37:22</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837783027003&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837783027003&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

I kept meaning to install the 'bogus wildcard' filter into BIND but
other things kept coming up.  Then I 'lost' my nameserver three times
in 24 hours due to a bogus wildcard.  Friday (Oct 28) I installed the
filter!

Since then:

Oct 28 01:22:12 swan named<A NAME="-66"></A><A HREF="#66">[66]</A>: Bogus wildcard from 128.248.2.50:
Oct 28 16:25:54 swan named<A HREF="#66">[66]</A>: Bogus wildcard from 128.248.2.50:
Oct 28 22:39:31 swan named<A HREF="#66">[66]</A>: Bogus wildcard from 128.248.2.50:
Oct 31 11:27:28 swan named<A HREF="#66">[66]</A>: Bogus wildcard from 128.248.2.50:
Oct 31 11:27:30 swan named<A HREF="#66">[66]</A>: Bogus wildcard from 128.248.2.50:
Oct 31 13:14:28 swan named<A HREF="#66">[66]</A>: Bogus wildcard from 128.248.2.50:
Oct 31 13:17:05 swan named<A HREF="#66">[66]</A>: Bogus wildcard from 128.248.2.50:

These are from UICVM.UIC.EDU, which is a VM machine.  It's trying to
tell me that * is served by NS.NASA.GOV (that's what kept popping up
in my cache).

Is this a local configuration problem or something deep in the
software?  Is there a known fix?  I'm happy (they're being filtered)
but how many others are being bombarded?

..Bob

